2137	f4eca49f-1f7e-4631-ae17-39e900c24bbb	2017-08-16 16:50:54	2017-08-16 16:50:54	0eb0e37e-6d02-4d0f-b63f-4e8bd3c1d875	1	1	{"RemoteUniqueID":"http:\\/\\/findingaids.folger.edu\\/dfobagot.xml#La266","name":"Letter from Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law) to Richard Bagot","dateCreated":"1591\\/2? February 12","description":"Detailed account of technical difficulties in settling the late Earl of Essex's estate. Hopes to leave London soon for Blithfield. Stafford quarter sessions have committed Mr. Dyet. Wants Mr. Eyre to get possession of Broughton's house in Lichfield now occupied by Sir Christopher Blount. Raleigh is gay in London but not at Court. Gelly Meyrick has abandoned a trip to view Wigmore Castle with the Earl.","folgerCallNumber":"L.a.266","format":"text","folgerGenre":"letters","agent":[{"name":"Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law)","description":"creator"},{"name":"Richard Bagot","description":"recipient"}],"inLanguage":"eng","folgerRelatedItems":[{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39488","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 recto","mpso":736,"description":"digital image"},{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39489","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 verso || leaf 2 recto","mpso":737,"description":"digital image"},{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39490","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 2 verso","mpso":738,"description":"digital image"}]}
2138	ba048fe7-8232-46da-930c-b048a96308cc	2017-08-16 16:50:54	2017-08-16 16:50:54	24c63cd9-afa3-4daf-9acf-783a6b029d62	1	1	{"RemoteUniqueID":"http:\\/\\/findingaids.folger.edu\\/dfobagot.xml#La267","name":"Letter from Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law) to Richard Bagot","dateCreated":"1592\\/3 March 5","description":"Essex sworn of the Privy Council. Will see the auditor about Bagot's accounts; fees of stewardship not to be allowed until the patent is enrolled. Essex in great favor because of speeches in Parliament and in the Council; he says he will soon pay his debts. Sir Edward Aston should consider carefully before plowing the warren at Chartley; Essex has a customary right to a free warren there and has exercised it for many years. What Essex will do about Leicester House and Uttoxeter Moors is unknown, but the fate of the Moors rests with the Earl of Huntingdon, who is gone toward York. Broughton's wife is sick.","folgerCallNumber":"L.a.267","format":"text","folgerGenre":"letters","agent":[{"name":"Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law)","description":"creator"},{"name":"Richard Bagot","description":"recipient"}],"inLanguage":"eng","folgerRelatedItems":[{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39491","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 recto","mpso":739,"description":"digital image"},{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39492","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 verso","mpso":740,"description":"digital image"}]}
2139	08967c03-a2d8-4120-be16-2878f45ac297	2017-08-16 16:50:54	2017-08-16 16:50:54	910fc1da-0ae9-4290-b607-94c7e40bc72b	1	1	{"RemoteUniqueID":"http:\\/\\/findingaids.folger.edu\\/dfobagot.xml#La268","name":"Letter from Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law) to Richard Bagot","dateCreated":"1592\\/3 March 7","description":"The Parliament, considering the state of things in Europe and expecting an attempted invasion, may be expected to pass a subsidy more than double. All who love their country should pay willingly. It is complained in Parliament that the burden of subsidies falls mainly on the inferior sort, but nothing will be done. Essex is sworn of the Privy Council. Sir Walter Harcourt promises full payment to Broughton by the hand of Sir Christopher Blount. A writ of habeas corpus for Thomas Fitzherbert is directed to the sheriff of Derbyshire, and Parliament will consider the cause of his imprisonment; his outlawry could not stand in the way of his election. Mr. Wakering has been to Broughton about Godwin's copyhold. If the Parliament ends soon, he expects to be in the country before the Stafford assizes.","folgerCallNumber":"L.a.268","format":"text","folgerGenre":"letters","agent":[{"name":"Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law)","description":"creator"},{"name":"Richard Bagot","description":"recipient"}],"inLanguage":"eng","folgerRelatedItems":[{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39493","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 recto","mpso":741,"description":"digital image"},{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39494","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 verso","mpso":742,"description":"digital image"},{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","fo