2140	b3e735d0-826a-4003-9d6f-1b9be5e82034	2017-08-16 16:50:54	2017-08-16 16:50:54	88680f1d-3645-4229-bc4f-d755661acfe8	1	1	{"RemoteUniqueID":"http:\\/\\/findingaids.folger.edu\\/dfobagot.xml#La269","name":"Letter from Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law) to Richard Bagot","dateCreated":"1592\\/3 March 14","description":"The Parliament is devising stiffer laws against recusants; also is expected to pass a treble subsidy and six fifteenths. Expects to be in the country soon - at Bridgenorth assizes. His wife is recovered. The Parliament issued a habeas corpus for Thomas Fitzherbert. He gives details of parliamentary procedure. Essex is in the House of Lords. Expects, with Mr. Auditor King, to end Bagot's account. The new Staffordshire commission of the peace has the name of young Mr. Lane. Parson Cradock has used George Devereux ill: Sir Edward Littleton is arbitrating; Fowler has won his case; Cradock has been borrowing money fraudulently.","folgerCallNumber":"L.a.269","format":"text","folgerGenre":"letters","agent":[{"name":"Richard Broughton (Richard Bagot's son-in-law)","description":"creator"},{"name":"Richard Bagot","description":"recipient"}],"inLanguage":"eng","folgerRelatedItems":[{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39497","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 recto","mpso":745,"description":"digital image"},{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39498","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 1 verso","mpso":746,"description":"digital image"},{"@id":"DAP internal ID for the following rootfile","folgerRemoteIdentification":{"folgerRemoteUniqueID":"39499","folgerRemoteSystemID":"luna"},"folgerRelationshipType":"included image","folgerObjectType":"image","label":"leaf 